item.title: Need help with client.java error
item.dc:creator: @beast14 beast14
item.description:
@beast14 wrote:

[quote=“matzie, post:8, topic:544705”][quote author=ohokay link=topic=663582.msg4434891#msg4434891 date=1404753308]
Use a cast

double d = 3.5; //int i = d; <- will give you a lossy conversion error int i = (int) d; System.out.println("Cast to integer " + i);
[/quote]
You have absolutely no clue what is going on here.

OT: This error must be misrepresented in some way shape or form. I put the array into my client and it doesn’t see any format errors. Your error must be somewhere else, or you forgot to save. My first thought was you put a decimal instead of a comma somewhere but there are none to be seen. Did you change something else? Are you by chance looking in a different file than the server is? (Different directory)[/quote]

I have fixed the problem thank you guys very much. This is a much better site than rune-server I posted there no one responded they didn’t even know what it was. Thank you guys!!
